instructions: Add a worksheet with this format for each age model you want to ChronRate
Fill in these columns with appropriate data
Unneeded columns can be left blank
short_name: One or two words to label the chronology
material score: from 1-5, see text for details
age_type: use "14C" for radiocarbon ages on specific materials, and "14C_bulk" for radiocarbon ages on bulk sediments. Label other age types as desired.
depths - enter either top and bottom depth, or mid-point depth
cal age: enter ages for non-radiocarbon dates, or optionally the calibrated age
cal age error:enter the 1-sigma uncertainty for calibrated and non 14C ages
rejected: include and mark (e.g., with an "x") which ages were rejected
